  "text": "In this study, we report a novel role for SIRT6 as a repressor of Mstn and muscle atrophy. SIRT6 is highly expressed in skeletal muscle tissue [CITATION_1] and has been shown to influence metabolic as well as inflammatory pathways [CITATION_2] .",
